Description
Your Talent. Our Vision. At Anthem, Inc., it’s a powerful combination, and the foundation upon which we’re creating greater access to care for our members, greater value for our customers, and greater health for our communities. Join us and together we will drive the future of health care.  
 
Product Management Director (Life & Disability)
Location:  Any US Location


As a Product Management Director, you will be responsible for leading the development, implementation, and management of our Life, Disability and Absence Management product strategies. Primary duties to include, but are not limited to: 
  
Develops, implements and maintains competitive product platform.  
Partners with product, sales and functional area managers and project team to achieve superior execution of product strategy in the marketplace.  
Tracks individual product performance by benefit design, market segment and geography.  
Supports the development of short and long term strategic product plans in support of market, sales and profitability objectives.  
Identifies system needs to support short and long term product strategy.  
May lead effort or manage project teams in the implementation of regional and companywide initiatives including legislative changes, vendor changes, claim management program and policy initiatives, contract enhancements, etc. 


Qualifications
Requires a BA/BS degree; 5-8 years of product development/management experience; or any combination of education and experience, which would provide an equivalent background within the group life and/or disability insurance sector. Demonstrated results in three or more of the following areas required: Product Development, Market Strategy, Market Research or Risk Management. Highly effective written, verbal and presentation skills, along with strong critical thinking skills and demonstrated ability to lead/influence cross-functional teams key to success in this role. MBA preferred.



