Diversity


Just like the health care service and solutions we provide, Anthem’s commitment to diversity is comprehensive. In our thinking and our actions, diversity informs and influences nearly every decision we make, and impacts every interaction with those we serve, including:

Diversity in Our Workplace
Diversity in Our Community
Supplier Diversity

Our dedication is evident in the recognition and awards we’ve received from leading publications and organizations. But it’s perhaps best articulated in the words and deeds of Anthem, Inc.’s own associates.
A Message from our Chief Diversity Officer
At Anthem, Inc., we are committed to sustaining a unified, inclusive culture. We see diversity and inclusion as essential to building high-performing teams, solving business challenges, effectively serving our customers, and delivering best-in-class solutions. Learn More

Our workforce accurately reflects the diverse backgrounds, cultures and health care needs of the customers and communities we serve. Our associates’ experiences, insights and passion help Anthem, Inc. gain a deeper understanding of how we can best provide services, programs and products that address the pressing needs and health care challenges of our customers. Our Associate Resource Groups help ensure diversity permeates every aspect of our business, which enables the ideas and perspectives of all associates to influence business solutions and drive the future of health care.
We are proud to serve millions of members across America. Supporting our communities with products and services that meet their unique needs is critical to our success. We are committed to being our customers’ valued and trusted health partner; to delivering the care management and benefits they can count on; and to demonstrating that commitment through our partnerships with diverse providers and suppliers in our members’ communities.
I invite you to learn more about us, and about how your talents can make a difference in a diverse range of career opportunities with Anthem, Inc
Sincerely,
Tracy Edmonds, Chief Diversity Officer




Diversity Events
We invite you to visit us at one of our diversity events and learn about how we’re transforming health care as part of our vision to be America’s valued health partner. For a full listing of events please click here.

 






   

 

